President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key positions in his Administration. These include Holly W. Greaves as Chief Financial Officer of the Environmental Protection Agency, Josephine Olsen as Director of the Peace Corps, Anne M. White as Assistant Secretary of Energy (Environmental Management), Marco M. Rajkovich Jr. as a Member and Chairman of the Federal Mine Safety and Health Review Commission, Marie Royce as Assistant Secretary of State (Educational and Cultural Affairs), William Roper as Assistant Secretary of the Air Force (Acquisition), and Kevin Fahey as Assistant Secretary of Defense (Acquisition).